Q.1 Write about application packaging

Answer: Application packaging is the process of preparing software so it can be easily installed on many computers the same way every time. 
Instead of manually installing apps, IT teams create a "package" that includes the installer, settings, and anything else the app needs. 
This helps make deployment faster and cleaner. It's mostly used in companies to save time and avoid errors. Tools like MSI/MSIX and App-V are often used. 
The main goal is simple: make the app work right everywhere, every time.

Q.2 Steps to install MSIX
Answer: 
  To install MSIX (Microsoft Software Installation eXchange) :
  I) Open microsoft store
  II) search for MSIX
  III) click on "get"
  IV) wait for installation
  V) open after installation
  VI) done
